Anyone with rudimentary knowledge of math and the game system will see that Jolt and Cinder Jolt are STATIC.  Cinder Jolt is higher, so it does a bit more anti-hate, it also saves versus another stat, which is fire, which MAY help in Velious more than straight-up magic would.<br>
<br>
But again, both are STATIC.  Both will ALWAYS remove 500 and 600 hate points, EVERY time the spell is cast and NOT RESISTED.<br>
<br>
Evade will do **AT LEAST** 500 points reduction, and that is only if the points it *WOULD HAVE* reduced was *LESS THAN* 500.<br>
<br>
Since rogues generate enough hate to choke a horse, having to worry about &quot;only 500 hate&quot; is not an issue, because at any given time the hate we'll need to reduce is a metric assload of hate-points greater than 500.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately you don't seem to see this, evade will work, maybe not as well as it does now, but it will still work.  It's been tested, only Kendrick died, and admittedly it was his own fault he died.<br>
<br>
I like that, you get assbeat because it's your fault.  *shrug*<br>
<br>
So, do us all a favor and shut up.  Nobody cares anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxsorus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xsorus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/01 2:28:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zen and the Art of Evade Mechanics</span><hr size=1> Now lets see here<br>
